<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06295181 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06295181 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Grove  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  COMPUTER; ELECTRONICS; LAS-VEGAS; TRADE; SHOW; OPENING; SEMICONDUTOR; COMPANY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Intel Corp. chief executive Andrew Grove says the personal computer of the1990s needs to become a communications tool as vital to business users as thetelephone -- and at his keynote speech at today's huge Comdex trade show,he'll try to prove it can.;   Instead of the usual canned speech with a fewslides of market figures, Grove has spent three months working with Intelengineers and 15 other companies on a complicated live demo that he says willculminate with actual Intel managers using personal computers equipped withwireless modems to solve an emergency at an Intel plant in Ireland.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business Monday  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  CIRCUS OF CIRCUITSIN THE CENTER RINGGROVE'S FLASHY DEMONSTRATION SHOWS WHAT PERSONALCOMPUTERS WILL DO  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Cover Story; See also related stories on page 1D in this section  </MEMO><TEXT>     Grove said the demo would illustrate his concept of &quot;just-in-timebusiness,&quot; where networks of computers permit firms to quickly exchange thepictures, voice messages and data needed to solve problems at anyorganizational level as they occur.;   &quot;There's a future in this old dog of aPC,&quot; Grove said.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  RORY J. O'CONNOR, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911021  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  167  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday, October 21, 199100295181,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>